"Oh, les baleines! Ha! Ha! Ha!"

42:52.319 --> 42:54.329
"Ce n'est pas la bonne saison."

42:55.507 --> 42:58.886
- What? Sorry?
- No whales. No whales.

42:59.637 --> 43:00.486
What?

43:00.521 --> 43:03.760
Wrong season. No whales.

43:11.063 --> 43:14.502
Don't listen to him.
We're going to see some.

43:15.840 --> 43:19.951
Seriously, just keep watching,
you're going to see one, I know it.

43:24.683 --> 43:26.474
Here, would you like to try?

43:48.716 --> 43:49.981
- Hey.
- Hey.

43:51.145 --> 43:54.488
- Have you come to a conclusion?
- Yes, I have.

43:57.296 --> 43:59.143
Are you going to share it?

44:01.267 --> 44:02.754
The trials should continue.

44:03.348 --> 44:05.384
What about the Ricci and Peterson kids?

44:05.635 --> 44:07.737
We couldn't connect
their deaths to the treatment.

44:10.720 --> 44:12.754
Oh. Okay, so Booker's clean?

44:15.580 --> 44:17.724
We weren't asked to judge Booker.

44:17.825 --> 44:20.127
We were asked to judge his trial.

44:21.001 --> 44:23.093
I can't know his motivation,

44:23.271 --> 44:25.426
but I know his biology and it's good.

44:25.896 --> 44:27.926
Even if he is a pompous asshole.

44:31.678 --> 44:34.226
But, you know, remenber,
these are trials, so...

44:34.684 --> 44:36.192
All I'm saying right now is that

44:36.193 --> 44:39.668
there's no reason
to say the treatment is bad.

44:40.248 --> 44:43.312
These are very sick kids, so,
is the drug going to save them?

44:43.600 --> 44:45.963
It saved 6 of them,
we need to keep studying it.

44:46.251 --> 44:48.744
- But folding might still be right?
- Sure.

44:48.836 --> 44:50.857
And more kids may die?

44:51.143 --> 44:56.279
Yeah. But, ultimately, this treatment
could save many lives, so...

44:57.214 --> 44:59.518
I don't know how you do it.

45:00.094 --> 45:03.063
- How do you play God?
- Oh, I try not to.

45:03.541 --> 45:05.653
This was your idea, remember?

45:16.048 --> 45:17.257
Oh my God!

45:17.937 --> 45:19.758
Look! I think I see a whale!

45:20.240 --> 45:22.792
Seriously, look, look!
Mick, can you see it?

45:24.858 --> 45:26.026
Mick?

45:28.351 --> 45:29.234
Mick?

45:31.618 --> 45:33.210
Mick? Mick?

46:24.230 --> 46:27.422
Hello, Sarah, it's me.
She's fine, sort of.

46:28.042 --> 46:30.833
A friend of hers died and she's...

46:31.401 --> 46:35.960
No, no, no, natural causes, but
she really needs you out here right now.

46:36.365 --> 46:39.581
- How come you're in Toronto?
- My God! You look so grown up!

46:39.852 --> 46:41.945
Look, I just lost my friend...

46:42.079 --> 46:43.464
my best friend!

46:46.160 --> 46:48.353
All you care about is
putting each other down.

46:48.667 --> 46:49.549
Lilith.

46:50.833 --> 46:53.218
The CIA got intercepts
of a plan to create a black out

46:53.570 --> 46:56.303
and use the chaos to move
terrorists from Canada to the U.S.

46:56.380 --> 46:57.686
Right, blame Canada!

46:58.166 --> 47:01.676
So, underground wires
seemingly spontaneously combust.

47:01.735 --> 47:03.448
And why do they think it's terrorism?

47:03.508 --> 47:05.139
I don't know.
Because that's what you do these days.

47:05.408 --> 47:07.200
You know who's really happy
about this black out?

47:07.532 --> 47:08.248
Who?

47:08.507 --> 47:10.836
That guy on death row who was supposed
to get the chair this morning.

47:11.507 --> 47:14.269
Caroline? There's
been another explosion.

47:14.370 --> 47:15.004
Chicago.

